1D pass 1H pass 1NT pass 2C pass 2D pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "69736e156bb4f41613bd5959a630abcaa8134606800c3abeb6c23089c4c09e2d"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/advanced_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST bids 2\C as New Minor Forcing, hoping EAST has three \Hs.

EAST does not have three \Hs and he has no other bid to make that 
will describe his hand any better. He cannot bid Notrump again without a \C stopper. 
So EAST rebids the 5-card \D suit.

WEST has nowhere to go, so passes.}

[Event ""]
